  "prompt": "I work in a hotel. My manager keeps the fire alarm off. Is it legal?",
  "response": "Whether it's legal for a hotel manager to keep the fire alarm off depends on local laws and regulations regarding fire safety. In many jurisdictions, fire alarms are required to be operational at all times in commercial buildings, including hotels, to ensure the safety of guests and staff. \n\nIf the fire alarm system is intentionally disabled, it could pose serious safety hazards and may be a violation of fire codes or regulations. It\u2019s essential to report any concerns about fire safety to local authorities or fire safety regulators, as this could endanger lives.\n\nIf you are concerned about the legality or safety practices in your hotel, consider discussing the issue with your manager or seeking advice from a professional in fire safety or a legal advisor who understands your local laws.",
